Diagonal:2, Size:2
[4]Eucharius was sent to Gaul by Saint Peter as bishop, together with the deacon Valerius and the subdeacon Maternus, to preach the Gospel.They came to the Rhine and to Ellelum (Ehl) in Alsace, where Maternus died.
[6]St. Peter gave his pastoral staff to Eucharius, and, upon being touched with it, Maternus, who had been in his grave for forty days, returned to life.
